								<div class="title" id="post-title-4109617">
																		The Cycle
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163469" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;" >djkaktus</a></span> <span class="odate time_1546719144 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">05 Jan 2019 20:12</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4109617">
									

<div style="text-align: center;">
<blockquote>
<p>And following our will and wind<br />
We may just go where no one's been.<br />
We'll ride the spiral to the end<br />
And may just go where no one's been.<br />
<span style="font-size:80%;"><em>Tool - Lateralus</em></span></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<p>This is four and a half years of work that I can finally tie into one neat little package. Each of these entries are canon with each other, and each builds off of those that came before it.</p>
<p>This would not have been possible without a number of people, namely my collaborator TwistedGears, my good friends ARD, Hippo, Jekeled, Joreth, Shaggy, Kirby, and so many others who either put eyes on or gave contributions to these entries during their conceptions.</p>
<p>I know I said this was a three part deal at the beginning of The Way It Ends, but I lied. It felt much better to me to bring it all together and call it a done deal.</p>
<p>Thanks again to everyone. I love this place, and I love all of you.</p>

							</div>

								
